2:54 hmmm so the was when Sana suddenly entered the scene.......vv suspicious

I feel some possible motives for the members would be:
Momo- she used to be his bandmate so she definitely knew a lot about him. But now she's suddenly a chorus singer so maybe he sabatoged her career to help boost/save his own career???
Dahyun- He probably stole a song she wrote and credited it as his own. I'm guessing the song became a hit which definitely would help his popularity and gain him a lot of money. 
Tzuyu- Her motive is honestly pretty tricky cause there's a lot of possible motives. Like since her name is 'Joe Road' she could be a road manager. And in the industry road managers are known to be treated the poorest and most unfairly, especially the younger ones, so I guess its revenge?

author: @kshinichi2637
text:
Tzuyu is usually competitive and serious in some TTT episodes but she's just laughing most of the time in this episode. Perhaps she can't take the game seriously because she's the perpetrator and she finds it hilarious that her unnies are being suspicious and blaming each other?

Same goes for Sana, she's so quiet the whole time. Is it to not accidentally blurt out something that would make her suspicious since she was given an important role? We all know she is clumsy and talkative. She's also the director of the showcase and there were some hints about 'stage lift' and only the director, among all of them, is knowledgeable about it...

I also don't think it's CEO Im. She needed Na Gasu at the very moment because as we all know, the company has a huge deficit. She could use Na Gasu's fame at least to make huge profit. But there's also a possibility she holds a grudge towards Na Gasu, maybe he has something to do with the company being in that state.

The coincidence of Dahyun's song and the case of Na Gasu is also questionable.

author: @sjihyo_
text:
Top suspects:
1.Mina- we all know she doesn't talk much but she's too silent here. She doesn't help out in finding evidence and just focusing on one. And Mina's messages sent to Na Gasu "I will take your funeral photo, and when am I gonna get paid" and also when she arrived she was rushing to leave
2. Chaeyoung- the reason why I think she's also a suspect to bc  she was the last person who Na Gasu saw and I think she could've did it.
3. Tzuyu- she laughs for NO reason and no one will laugh if someone is missing unless.....
4.Nayeon-Na Gasu alr has big deficit and the company is going bankrupt. Maybe she's there for the money?
5.Jeong- as seen here, Jeongyeon finds a lot of clues and she's writing something on the paper that she's holding. When Nayeon told her to "Show it!", Jeongyeon literally shook like she's hiding something
6.Jihyo- the note that said "if u cant be mine then d*e"(found by Sana),and "if I cant have u then d*e"(found by DH) JH is the president of the fanclub and maybe its her?
7.Sana-she is just focusing on one evidence and not helping and she was on the phone when they were seated on front of the stage so maybe she hired someone to get rid of Na Gasu?

author: @danorais8604
text:
If we really talk about the evidences and suspicions about members, Jihyo, Mina, Nayeon are the suspicious. Let's include Dahyun. 
Jihyo is a pharmacist students, meaning she has an entire and easy access on different kinds of drugs or other chemicals that she can use on kidnapping Nagasu. And she used her fandom president's position to be close with Nagasu and put her plan in motion. But she didn't have a motive. Or she have but will reveal later. But, it's common when you're part of a fandom, the obsession is present. So that's one of her motive.

Mina- Mina's might be joking on the funeral photo. She also didn't have motive to kidnap Nagasu or might also reveal in later episodes.

Nayeon- She's Nagasu's CEO. And Nayeon's not paying Nagasu might be a motive. Nagasu might threatened her to file a lawsuit against her because of her, not paying Nagasu a enough money.

Dahyun- I really want to know the lyrics of "DEATH" There might be some clues out there that will help the investigators in the future to find the culprit.  Can't find anything at all. Or I may have missed something in the episode.

Other members are also suspicious, especially Momo, I can't really put my touch on Momo's presence this time. She's a former member of Tiger Moth, I think she knew something but something or someone is stopping her to reveal the truth. So hard to create theories now, the motives and evidences are all over the place. It's so messy 😂 Nayeon was too loud 😂

1. He was hit by a blunt object (probably the head will do), then blood will come out. 
2. He was stabbed or hit by a sharp object, any part of the body will do. 
3. It was a fake clue

Maybe he was taped first, stabbed by the killer, disposed his body and didn't have the time to hide the evidence.

Now, where is the weapon used?

Was it hidden somewhere, disposed or the perpetrator is still holding onto it?

author: @TalkingAboutYooh
text:
Interesting info about the name of Tiger Moth's leader Na Gasu.
In Hangul, naga su means be out.
In Japanese, nagasu means shed.
In Hausa, na gah su means I see them.

Given the recent album title Eyes Wide Open, that last meaning is interesting, if unintentional.

text:
Some people that I lowkey suspect are:
Nayeon, she keeps avoiding eye contact when talking so that can be a sign she's lying? And she seems like she's avoiding any sus on her and pushing the sus to someone else.
Momo: I dunno man, she just sus.
The people who are most probably not the culprit:
Jihyo: she legitimately looks shook when the case happened and seemed really excited to see nagasu before the case happened, she does look like one of those saesung fans but that would be too obvious then.
Tzuyu: she's uhhh, just looks innocent???
Chaeyoung: she found some of the most helpful clues, I don't thing she'd bother helping if she was the culprit.
Jeongyeon : she's a little sus but I don't think it's her by the way she just talks and all.
Dahyun: she seemed pretty shook when the case happened and the way she's helping to find clues, it can't be her.
My PRIME suspects are: 
Sana: see how she came so sus just smiling, she didn't talk with anyone at the beginning, she didn't help find that many clues, she just looked at one clue, she didn't seem that shook but rather happy when the case was announced. 
Mina: she seems to get pretty defensive when someone suspects her and she's REALLY sus.

text:
Y'all wanna here my guess on who is the person behind this?

Ok I'ma go full on 500 IQ here.


So based on the things they found, the letters and blood, it could be Jihyo since the letters says how much *"unknown"* wants to be with him. _BUT_ my theories suspected *MOMO* because she was a former co-member of him (3:25 , 6:52). Maybe she got jealous of him after the disbandment, you could see that's she's not as excited as the others, maybe she went there to just pretend to attend. AND, since she's an ex-member, she knows how fans and sasaengs are like, think about it guys, she's the one who planned all of this, she made the letters and targeted Jihyo. Jihyo's resume was there, since Momo being the ex-member, she knows how much of a fan she is and began researching about her background, and once she founds out about Jihyo being the president of the club Momo began all of this and frame Jihyo and the others. _AND_ the fact that Momo was late makes it even more suspicious.  *MY GUESS, MOMO.*

If y'all have guesses also let's brainstorm before the end of this series.
